attention with counterplay.} (12... Qb6 $5 13. b3 Nf6 14. Qxd6 Rd8 15. Qa3 Nd4
16. Ne3 Ng4 17. Rc1 Nxe3 18. fxe3 Nc6 19. c5 $13 {Black gets compensation for
his pawn... but he has lack of space for piece mobility in the centre...
White's next plan is to play g3, Be2 and 0-0, with a reasonable game - a pawn
up.}) 13. O-O-O Qb6 14. f4 {White moves his f-pawn from the eye of the Black
queen... it also provokes Black into taking on f4, so as to gain control over
the key d4 and f4 squares for his knights...} exf4 $6 {An inaccuracy: 14..Bg4
