Followed by Rf1 and pressure on f5 is visible...}) 15. Qxd6 Rd8 16. Qxf4 Rxd1+
{Black hopes to get compensation for the lost pawns...} 17. Nxd1 O-O 18. Nc3
Rc8 $44 (18... Qc5 $6 19. Qe3 Qe5 20. Bd3 Rc8 21. Nd5 Bxd5 22. exd5 Nb4 23. Rd1
Nxd3+ 24. Rxd3 $14) 19. Nd5 $5 {White tries to simplify the position and gain
