1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 e5 5. Nb5 {Basic idea of this 5.Nb5
move is to attack on the d6 square, so that White gets a tempo to be able to
play 6.c4 and thus dominate the d5 square forever!} d6 6. c4 {Basic idea
behind this pawn formation for White is: (i) to play a4,b4-b5 and, if Black
takes a6xb5, then White will re-take with c4xb5, thus creating a passed pawn
along the queen side; (ii) to place a knight on d5 followed by a pawn storm
along the queen side and try to create a passed pawn there. For this, White
has to take a little care - he should avoid c5xd6 and try to play c6 instead
for creating a passed pawn on the queen side...} Be7 7. N1c3 a6 8. Na3 Be6 9.
Bd3 (9. Nc2 $5 {Sensible move indeed... improving the offside knight and
preventing Black's possible Nd4 for the time being; also waiting to develop
the light-squared bishop depending on what unfolds next. For details, please
go through the Theory Section.}) 9... Nf6 10. O-O O-O 11. Nc2 Rc8 12. Nd5 {
Forcing Black to take on d5 so as to gain a pawn majority on the queen side...}
Nd7 13. b4 {White implements his next plan, i.e. a pawn march along the queen
side!} Bg5 14. a3 g6 15. Kh1 {Prophylactic move... preparing f4...} Bxc1 16.
Rxc1 Ne7 17. Qd2 {Connecting the rooks... monitoring the dark squares in
Black's camp.} f5 18. Nce3 f4 19. Nxe7+ Qxe7 20. Nd5 Qh4 21. f3 Kh8 22. Kg1 Rc6
23. Qb2 Qg5 24. Rf2 h5 25. Rfc2 Rfc8 26. a4 {White tries to implement his plan
with no delay whatsoever!} a5 $2 {Violating the principle of "don't make pawn
moves where you are weaker".} 27. c5 $1 dxc5 28. bxa5 Bxd5 29. exd5 Rd6 30.
Qxb7 {White successfully creates a strong passer on the flank...} Qd8 31. Qb2
Rxd5 32. Be4 Rd6 33. Bb7 $6 (33. Rd2 $1 Nf6 34. Rxd6 Qxd6 35. Bb7 {Is a win
for White...}) 33... Rb8 34. Qb5 Nf6 35. Rf1 $6 (35. Re1 $1 Rd1 36. Rc1 $14)
35... Rd1 (35... Nd5 $1 36. a6 Ne3 37. a7 Nxc2 38. axb8=Q Qxb8 39. Qxc5 Rd2 {
With counterplay for Black...}) 36. a6 Qd4+ 37. Kh1 c4 $4 {Looking good... but
he doesn't know what he missed in this position!} (37... Qxa4 $3 38. Qe2 Rxf1+
39. Qxf1 Qxc2 40. a7 Rd8 $19 {Now Black gets the winning position..}) 38. Rc1
Rxf1+ 39. Rxf1 Qd3 40. Qb1 Qd4 41. Rd1 Qe3 42. Qxg6 Rf8 43. Qh6+ Kg8 44. a7 $18
{The game is over...} Qxa7 45. Rd7 Nxd7 46. Bd5+ Rf7 47. Qg6+ Kh8 48. Bxf7 1-0

